AIM

To write a Python program that demonstrates different list operations such as accessing elements, adding new items, copying lists, extending lists, searching elements, sorting, reversing, deleting items, counting elements and slicing lists.

Algorithm

Begin the program.
Create a list containing employee information.
Display a specific element using its index position.
Take a role from the user and add it to the list.
Print all items of the list using a loop.
Create a duplicate copy of the list and display it.
Add another list of employee details using extend.
Search and display the position of a given element using index.
Arrange the list elements in sorted order.
Reverse the order of the list.
Remove the last element using pop.
Find how many times a particular element appears.
Extract a part of the list using slicing and display it.
Terminate the program.

SOURCE CODE

list1 = ["5G","mobile network","wireless technology","1G","2G","3G","4G","Gbps","data speeds","latency","wireless standard","network capacity","IoT","broadband","smartphones","VR","AR","uniform data","cost-per-bit","sensors","mobility","ultra reliable","communication","connectivity"]
